725771f-c.title: Queens: 104th Street - 48th Avenue
725771f-c.text:
104th Street, at the S.E. corner of 48th Avenue, showing St. Leos Roman Catholic Church and the rectory. The rectory
is at the N.W. corner of V9th Street.
P. L. Sperr  View 1 June 7, 1927
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 2,3: October 2, 1935

727481f-a.title: Queens: Nicholls Avenue - 104th Street
727481f-a.text:
102-53 Nicholls Avenue, adjoining the N. W. corner of 104th Street. This old house appears on an 1891.atlas of Corona. The property was owned by H. E. Sanford in 1873. The avenue was
then named Vine otreet.
P. L Sperr  October 2, 1935
